A Jos Upper Area Court sitting in Kasuwan Nama on Wednesday sentenced a 22-year-old driver, Abdul Abbas, to one-year imprisonment for stealing four cell phones and cash worth N223, 000 The Judge, Mr Yahaya Mohammed, sentenced Abbas after he pleaded guilty to a two-count charge of stealing and causing grievous hurt. Mohammed, however, gave the convict an option to pay N10,000 fine. ALSO READ: Jigawa warns against using pesticides for fish preservation Earlier, the police prosecutor, Insp. Ibrahim Gowkat told the court that the case was transferred from the Laranto Police Station, Jos, on Sept. 23, 2019, to the State’s Anti-Robbery Unit for investigation. Businessman in court for allegedly damaging N400,000… Man, 24, allegedly steals N250,000 gold chain at Tejuoso… N2.2bn fraud: Court rejects Fayose’s move to stop witness… Teenager in court for allegedly beating friend unconscious Gowkat said the defendant committed the offence with one other person still at large on Sept. 6 in Jos. He said that the defendant and his accomplice armed themselves with knives and other weapons and snatched the complainant’s, Mr Mubarak Musa, telephones. “They forcefully took the phones and money and in the process injured the complainant’s brother Mr Dayabu Abdullahi,” he said. Gowkat said the offence contravened Sections 59, 277 and 217 of the Plateau State Penal Code, Law of Northern Nigeria. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.